So, tell us about your experience moving or migrating someplace new.
Well, I moved to Chicago back in 2011 from Italy.
And what's funny is I am a quarter Swedish on my grandma's side, which is my mom's side.
So moving to Chicago is my first big move.
And I love it here. I've been here for 14 years.
However, I just never thought I would be living in the Swedish neighborhood.
But it's my favorite neighborhood.
And I'm really proud of that part of my heritage.
It's just such rich culture and Swedish people in general are just very nice, caring people.
And I'm very grateful to be living in this neighborhood.
And this is my first time at the Swedish Museum. I should have done this a long time ago.
